<br>
Heagan, It's called guildchat. of course they're going to mobilize faster than someone who has to work with tells. Experience may have something to do with it but I guarantee you it did not have as much an affect as this factor alone.<br>
<br>
Ultimately it comes down whether or not you have respect for another person's hard work, which is why I personally DO give a little more credence to an open raid than that of a Raiding Guild. There is no question that Blayze worked his but off, both in the camp, and trying to pull everyone together. This isnt to say AS didnt work hard as well but they had a bit more going in their favor to reduce the workload such as guildchat above. Open Raids are just plain hard work on the raid Leader, which is why you Won't see a gaggle of Clerics from the Open raid community trying to camp Ragefire, which is yet another reason why I would give slightly more credence to an open raider who actually is showing a raid capable force, its just not that common an occurence. Most Clerics would likely go your suggested route and join that Raiding guild instead if they wanted their epic. <br>
<br>
Now clearly there is room for abuse, i.e. if some solitary person camps some major spawn and then expects all others to wait while he takes the next two hours to assemble a force. That wasn't the case here.<br>
<br>
Heagan I both like and respect you in game, but here I must respectfully disagree.<br>
<br>
As for AS there is no question they played it by the rules. They also had taken Ragefire the previous two or three times wich is yet another reason I'm a little more sympathetic to Blayze and a little less to them. I have some good friends in AS and I don't plan to blacklist them or their guild. Yeah they played it by the rules, so do lawyers that doesn't mean we always like what they do with them.<br>
<br>
For Blayze ther only thing I can suggest is to get all your friends to<br>
<br>
/autojoin Blayzepic <br>
<br>
you still wont likely have as fast a response time, but it might help you be able to compete a little more.<br>
<br>
just my oppinion on the matter take care all and happy gaming<br>
